snippet.title: Khumar Episode 48 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - 27th April 2024 - Har Pal Geo
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Khumar Episode 48 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - Feroze Khan - Neelam Muneer - 27th April 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khumar Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints

Khumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.

Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from a
lower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.

Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.

What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?

7th Sky Entertainment Presentation 
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi 
Writer: Maha Malik
Director: Ali Faizan

Cast:
Feroze Khan as Faiz
Neelam Muneer as Hareem
Hina Bayat as Kehkasha Begum
Asma Abbas as Durdana
Behroz Sabzwari as Sheikh Furqan
Zainab Qayoom as Dil Araa
Shehryar Zaidi as Taufeeq
Adnan Samad as Nasir
Sheherzade Peerzada as Hamna  
Minsa Malik as Laiba 
Kinza Malik as Atiya
Mehmood Akhtar as Zaawar  
Agha Mustafa as Rayyan  
Hamzah Tariq as Rufi
Ayesha Rajpoot as Shagufta
Mizna Waqas as Husna
Sohail Masood as Mirza Sahab
Birjees Farooqui as Salma

snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Khumar 2nd Last Episode 49 Teaser - 27th April 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.

Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from a
lower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.

Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.

What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?

7th Sky Entertainment Presentation 
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi 
Writer: Maha Malik
Director: Ali Faizan

Cast:
Feroze Khan as Faiz
Neelam Muneer as Hareem

snippet.title: Shaadvik-‡Æì‡Æü Evening Routine | ‡ÆÖ‡Æµ‡Æ©‡ØÅ‡Æï‡Øç‡Æï‡ØÅ ‡Æá‡Æ©‡Øç‡Æ©‡ØÅ‡ÆÆ‡Øç formula milk ‡Æ§‡Æ±‡Øá‡Æ©‡Ææ ? | Hema's Diary
snippet.description:
üë∂üíï Hi everyone! Welcome back to Hema's Diary! In today's vlog, we're sharing our morning routine with our little one, featuring Aptamil Gold Stage 3 formula milk. As new parents, finding the best formula milk for our baby's growth and development is crucial, and we've chosen Aptamil Gold Stage 3 for its close resemblance to breast milk and the essential nutrients it provides. üçº‚ú®

Starting our day with some tender moments, we wake our baby gently and spend some quality time playing and chatting. Hydration is key, so we begin with some water before moving on to our formula milk routine. üåûüçº

In this video, I'll show you how we prepare and feed Aptamil formula milk, a great option for parents looking for lactose-free formula milk. We discuss why we trust Aptamil for its added prebiotics HMO that help in building our baby‚Äôs immunity and protecting against infections.

After feeding, it's bath time! üõÅüßº Join us as we navigate through the joys and challenges of babycare, from choosing the right diapers to ensuring a comfortable bath time. I also share some tips on how to handle colic in infants, a common issue many parents face.

Next, we're off for a stroll in the park. Check out our review of the latest in baby/newborn strollers, ensuring comfort and safety for our little adventurer on the go. üå≥üë∂

Mealtime is another highlight of our day. I'll take you through our feeding routine using our infant feeding chair, a lifesaver for keeping those wiggly moments in check while ensuring our baby is comfortable and secure.

Remember, breastfeeding is the best option for babies, but when that‚Äôs not possible, formula milk like Aptamil can be an excellent alternative. We hope this video helps new parents making these decisions and encourages a healthy, happy baby life.

Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to Hema's Diary for more insights into parenting, babycare, and product reviews. Hit the bell icon to stay updated on our latest videos! üîî‚ù§Ô∏è

snippet.title: Jiya Laage Na (Official Video) Shilpa Rao, Mohit Chauhan, Rochak Kohli | Isha Malviya,Parth Samthaan
snippet.description:
Presenting the official video of "Jiya Laage Na" composed by Rochak Kohli, and sung by the maestros Mohit Chauhan and Shilpa Rao, will envelope you with its warmth of love. Rochak has created a melody that inherently and effortlessly draws you in to its world. The words are simple, yet not simplistic, the symphony is gentle yet impactful, and the hook line provides the perfect bind in bringing all the emotions together.

The music video is shot with soft focus, featuring the most popular Parth Samthaan and Isha Malviya. It‚Äôs a simple story of a newly married couple finding love and each other in a joint family set-up. Its looking for tender moments of togetherness snatched away from everyone that captures the essence of the song.

Jiya Laage Na is that restless ode of love, of longing and finally, finding a common love language.

Create your shorts now: https://youtu.be/h6llRrdv-Ms

localized.title: Jiya Laage Na (Official Video) Shilpa Rao, Mohit Chauhan, Rochak Kohli | Isha Malviya,Parth Samthaan
localized.description:
Presenting the official video of "Jiya Laage Na" composed by Rochak Kohli, and sung by the maestros Mohit Chauhan and Shilpa Rao, will envelope you with its warmth of love. Rochak has created a melody that inherently and effortlessly draws you in to its world. The words are simple, yet not simplistic, the symphony is gentle yet impactful, and the hook line provides the perfect bind in bringing all the emotions together.

The music video is shot with soft focus, featuring the most popular Parth Samthaan and Isha Malviya. It‚Äôs a simple story of a newly married couple finding love and each other in a joint family set-up. Its looking for tender moments of togetherness snatched away from everyone that captures the essence of the song.

Jiya Laage Na is that restless ode of love, of longing and finally, finding a common love language.

Create your shorts now: https://youtu.be/h6llRrdv-Ms

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

Click here to watch all the episodes of 'Jo Jetha Wahi Sikander' : https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSXTaG1fT0cTWbYoG3SaD_hKNC0g53ugi
